create a one sheet for this music duo's upcoming debut album release and tour, using the following info: 
Introducing FLYING OCELOT

…duo Dani Oore (vox-winds) & Florian Hoefner (piano) unite for an unforgettable musical experience.

Their kinship and synergy explodes in exuberant melodious improvisations with harmonic sophistication and structural depth.

Raw, elegant, bold, fragile …and maybe playful. 

Daniel, a veteran of the late Jerry Granelli’s groups, and Florian leading his own JUNO-winning trio, perform across 5 continents collaborating with renowned artists (Kurt Rosenwinkel, Seamus Blake, Julian Priester, Dan Weiss, and Jay Clayton), garnering East Coast Music Awards, Juno nominations, the Stingray Rising Star Award, and the ASCAP Young Jazz Composer Award.

Their forthcoming debut album, ECSTASY OF BECOMING out SEPT 2023, on ALMA Records

…is a story of vulnerable transformation told in sounds dark and light.

Make magic with them as they embark post-pandemic on their first international tours.

HISTORY & collaboration:
Dani was familiar with Hoefner’s brilliance, from the latter’s visits to u of toronto. They were introduced a couple years later, and then daniel was a postdoc fellow with the international institute for critical studies in improvisation (IICSI) at Memorial U, where he and Florian first made music following the 2020 ‘snomaggedon’ a massive state of emergency shut down of the city, a month before the whole world shut down with covid. Those first performances were captured and the magic is still palpable. They later discovered they both had a common mentor-colleague in jerry granelli (Florian from his time at the Berlin Hoschule der musik and daniel growing up in halifax and later collaborations). They reached out to granelli who was equally excited and enthused to reconnect and collaborate with them in st. john’s. It was not to be however. First the pandemic and then jerry fell very ill and passed. Shortly before dani left newfoundland to the states, florian called him for a duo recording session. 

ALBUM details:

The album ‘exstasy of becoming’ out SEPT 2023, on ALMA Records
is a story of vulnerable transformation.

It wasn’t consciously planned that way. But listening back to the arc of the album, the story emerged. And dani wrote a poem, as he’s done for previous projects, that tries to capture one essence of the story in words.

Knowing that florian and dani had no compositions or material planned, helps to explain the vulnerability and transformation in facing that blank slate of the moment… 
So everything on the album is a first time. There are no second takes with this because the composition, the form, is about being present with one another in the space and with sounds of our moving bodies. 

The song —each song— is now. 

“The sounds reflect our bodies interacting with each other’s sounds and gestures… the musical instruments are tools, say like a pen and paper, and the musical ideas are words exploring relationships… the relationships between the musical words are ultimately about life relationships… the ups and downs of life. Music reflects life and experience… through our bodies… moving and making sound together.” 

“Our focus is on listening and sharing vulnerably and supportively. If we stop that, the music collapses, because there’s nothing else, there are no prepared compositions. In this context, even if we fall back on a lick or idea, a fancy word, it’s bad, it sticks out like a sore thumb, it’s the ego looking bad because it’s acting out of fear of looking bad. But evocative words emerge naturally in our conversation… there are moments where suddenly what we’re making feels to me like Joni or Keith, Strayhorn or Gasparian… and Florian will have distinct impressions reflecting his own experiences.”

The continuous two-part piece that closes the album is taken from a recording session we did with the same engineer in the same hall about six months earlier. The title evokes a spirit transformation at death. It starts as a wild and explosive piano and voice, and then the spirit gives up, it lets go into great gentleness. 
FUTURE: 
Our first duo performance you can hear the audience singing a lot with us. That’s a comical magical sacred thing that we’ve not done since the pandemic struck.
And we’re always exploring sounds/instruments, and our performances will reflect this too.
So we’re excited to continue to explore sharing and listening with people in canadian communities and hopefully beyond these borders.
The story of transformation told in our upcoming album has a part deux… sequel, that’s already been mixed and mastered, so we hope to release this soon. And then get back in the studio to make more things together.






