​​Lead Caps

Admissions representatives can ​​only receive a configured number of specific leads per day. To provide this functionality, a nightly process resets their Genesys skill proficiency as configured in the ​​[​Zulu Portal](https://zulu.ultimatemedical.edu/). The portal also provides toggling the functionailty on and off.

​Lead Cap Skill​

Currently, a "LeadCap" skill is assigned to all leads that came via eLeads, have today's lead date (day 0) and had no calls to them (no dial from an agent). An agent has to have "LeadCap" skill to be able to take the lead and proficiency value (1-100) levels out who the lead (call) gets routed to. The proficiency on the skill assigned to the agent decreases by one, as long as a contact was made with the prospective student (see Dispositions)​. Once the agent caps out (i.e. proficiency decreases to 0), the skill is removed from the agent and they no longer receive leads that have not been called yet.

​Day 0 Lead Cap Skill​

Currently, a "Day0LeadCap" skill is assigned to all leads that came via eLeads and have today's lead date (day 0). Unlike Lead Cap Skill, this limits the number of leads an agent can receive regardless the number of calls placed to a lead, as long as the lead has today's lead date. The proficiency on agent's skill decreases by one regardless of how they disposition the lead and once the agent caps out (i.e. proficiency decreases to 0), the skill is removed from the agent and they no longer receive day 0 leads.

​Day 0 Lead First Contact Cap Skill​

Currently, a "Day0LeadFirstContact" skill is assigned to all leads that came via eLeads, have today's lead date (day 0) and have not yet met certain contacted criteria (Contacted - Not Engaged, Unverified Lead or Do Not Call; see Dispositions). This limits the number of day 0 leads an agent can receive and disposition as contacted. The proficiency on agent's skill is decreased by one if an agent dispositions a day 0 lead that have not yet been dispositioned as Contacted - Not Engaged, Unverified or Do Not Call at least once.

